Defendant Felipe Arguello-Callejas in court with attorney Stephen Michael Govin.  Antonella Aleman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  BRANCH 20 FOR BRANCH 03:  Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record. The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms. Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. The Court imposed 12 months at the House of Correction, with Huber; good time allowed.  The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of 24 months.

 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - Remain controlled substance and alcohol free; may not use, sell or be around controlled substances;
 - Urine screens;
 - AODA assessment; treatment if needed;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Pay a $1,500.00 fine, plus DNA surcharge, costs, disbursements and supervision fees.  Failure to pay amounts in full by the end of probationary term would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.  
 - Court imposed 4 months condition time at the House of Correction as follows:  Serve 90 days at the House of Correction, with Huber for work; good time allowed.  Report date stayed to:  7/22/14 at 5:00 p.m.  The 30 days balance remaining is to be stayed and used by agent for non-compliance.

Should defendant complete all conditions set forth by this Court, the Department of Corrections; pay all the fines, costs and surcharges; and remain free and clear of the criminal justice system arising to the level of probable cause or greater, the Court would consider a petition for expungement.

Filed,
